---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { site } from '../config/site';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions — Chuck Allen"
  description="Terms and conditions for using chuckallen.dev."
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="section-container">
      <div class="prose">
        <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
        <p class="effective-date"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> July 8, 2026</p>

        <p>
          These Terms & Conditions ("Terms") govern your use of <a href="https://chuckallen.dev">chuckallen.dev</a>,
          operated by Chuck Allen ("I," "me," "my"). By accessing or using this site, you agree to be
          bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use this site.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Description of Site</h2>
        <p>
          This site is a professional portfolio and marketing site for web development services. It provides
          information about my services, experience, and how to get in touch. The site itself is informational —
          actual project work, deliverables, timelines, and payment terms are governed by separate written
          agreements between me and each client.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>No Client Relationship</h2>
        <p>
          Visiting this site, submitting the contact form, or booking a consultation call does not create a
          client relationship, contract, or obligation on either party. A client relationship begins only
          when both parties agree to a written scope of work or service agreement.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content on this site — including text, design, code, graphics, and logos — is the property of
          Chuck Allen unless otherwise noted. You may not copy, reproduce, distribute, or create
          derivative works from this site's content without prior written permission.
        </p>
        <p>
          Third-party trademarks, logos, and brand names referenced on this site (such as technology
          logos in the services section) remain the property of their respective owners and are used for
          identification purposes only.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use this site for any unlawful purpose</li>
          <li>Submit false, misleading, or malicious content through the contact form</li>
          <li>Attempt to interfere with the site's operation, security, or infrastructure</li>
          <li>Scrape, crawl, or harvest data from this site using automated tools</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the site or its systems</li>
        </ul>

        <hr />

        <h2>Contact Form and Communications</h2>
        <p>
          The contact form is provided as a convenience for reaching out about potential projects. By submitting
          the form, you consent to receiving a response via the email address you provide. I am not obligated to
          respond within a specific timeframe, though I make every effort to reply promptly during US business hours.
        </p>
        <p>
          Messages submitted through the contact form are delivered via Mailgun and processed in accordance
          with the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Scheduling and Consultations</h2>
        <p>
          Consultation calls are booked through Calendly, a third-party scheduling service. By booking a call,
          you agree to Calendly's <a href="https://calendly.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Terms of Use</a>.
          An initial consultation does not constitute a commitment to provide services.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
        <p>
          This site may contain links to third-party websites (LinkedIn, GitHub, Calendly, etc.). I am not
          responsible for the content, privacy practices, or terms of any third-party site. Visiting those
          links is at your own discretion.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          This site is provided <strong>"as is"</strong> and <strong>"as available"</strong> without warranties
          of any kind, either express or implied. I do not guarantee that the site will be uninterrupted,
          error-free, or free of harmful components. I make no warranties regarding the accuracy, reliability,
          or completeness of any content on this site.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, Chuck Allen shall not be liable for any indirect,
          incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of or inability to use
          this site. This includes, without limitation, damages for loss of profits, data, or other intangible
          losses — even if I have been advised of the possibility of such damages.
        </p>
        <p>
          My total liability for any claim arising from your use of this site shall not exceed the amount
          you paid to access the site (which is zero).
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Chuck Allen from any claims, damages, losses, or
          expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of your use of this site, your violation of
          these Terms, or your violation of any third party's rights.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Colorado, without regard to conflict of law principles.
          Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of this site shall be resolved exclusively in the
          state or federal courts located in Colorado.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Severability</h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable or invalid, that provision will be
          limited or removed to the minimum extent necessary, and the remaining provisions will remain in
          full force and effect.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          I may update these Terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated
          effective date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about these Terms, contact me at:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href={`tel:+1${site.phone}`}>{site.phoneFormatted}</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 8rem 0 4rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .legal-page h1 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .effective-date {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  /* --- Vertical rhythm overrides for legal content --- */

  .legal-page .prose hr {
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }

  .legal-page .prose h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal-page .prose h3 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-page .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-page .prose ul,
  .legal-page .prose ol {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .legal-page .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
  }
</style>
